Immigration

Armed ICE officers chase teacher into preschool in Chicago

The incident appears to be one of the first during Trump’s second administration in which immigration officers entered school grounds.

Updated
November 5, 2025 at 4:54 p.m. ESTyesterday at 4:54 p.m. EST
5 min
By Arelis R. Hernández

Immigration officers arrested a teacher early Wednesday in Chicago after chasing her into the grounds of a private preschool and grabbing her as parents and students looked on, according to a local official, witnesses and video footage of the incident.
